The burgers are great, but the service is so unbelievably bad that it is no where near worth it to ever go here. Let's just recap my most recent experience (among the many many poor experiences I've had here) as an example of what I mean. I call over and over with no answer. When they finally do answer, they put me on hold for 10 minutes then hang up on me. Eventually I get through to someone and order a burger and cheesy jerk fries. They tell me it will be 15 minutes. I drive to Mikkey's, and wait and wait and wait until finally my order comes out an hour after I had placed it. Keep in mind, the place is not even very busy at 10pm on a Sunday night. They hand me a bag, and I take it to go. At home I discover that they gave me the wrong order of fries again. The incompetency at Mikkey's is beyond acceptable.
